    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-05T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-05T02:00:00-05:00" n="477"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.001 Chiang Kai-shek/7–549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-05T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 5, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:53 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 689. President Li Tsung-jen tells me no meeting with Generalissimo has yet
                    been arranged. In view Li’s previous statement that if Generalissimo did not
                    come Canton he and Yen Hsi-shan would visit Generalissimo, it would seem
                    Generalissimo is the reluctant bride.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept Cantel 689, repeated Nanking 462, Shanghai 898.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
